helpdesk-ticket.subject: Matlab- Raspberry Pi 3 Question
helpdesk-ticket.description:
IT Staff:
We have several design teams that will be working on projects involving Matlab and the Raspberry Pi 3 (RPi 3) over the next few years.
According to the Mathworks website (http://www.mathworks.com/hardware-support/raspberry-pi-matlab.html?s_tid=srchtitle), Matlab Release 2016a or higher appears to be required for RPi 3 support. What are the schools update plans regarding Matlab. Specifically, will we likely move to 2016a this summer?
Also, downloading the Matlab Hardware Support Packages appears to require students provide Mathworks account information (mentioned in the “Install the MATLAB Support Package for Raspberry Pi<http://www.mathworks.com/videos/install-the-matlab-support-package-for-raspberry-pi-94266.html?type=shadow>” video linked from the Matlab Raspberry Pi hardware support page (http://www.mathworks.com/hardware-support/raspberry-pi-matlab.html?s_tid=srchtitle)). I think this is simply for their individual Mathworks account which that they can setup on their own, but I’d like this confirmed. I set up my account a long time ago and do not remember the information required.
Dr. Tritt

helpdesk-note.body: Called the user no response

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jennifer Farrell,
You can always stop by the helpdesk and we will be able to help you more efficiently, if you are unable to do that, you may just follow these steps:
1. Open "Control Panel" and then click on " Uninstall A Program " and this should give you the list of all installed apps on your laptop. 2. Select "Microsoft Office Professional Plus 2013" out of the list. 3. When you click it, A "Change" option comes right above it which is beside "Uninstall" Option 4. Click the "Change" Option and enter the following key (Case sensitive)
YC7DK-G2NP3-2QQC3-J6H88-GVGXT
5. Hit the "Next" Button, and let the setup go till the end. (Might take 10-15 minutes)
Happy to help!
Arush Arora IT Helpdesk Technician (414)277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Library Televisions Room 207
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello! Some students have indicated a problem projecting their laptop screens onto the televisions in room 207. Instead of displaying a screen to allow logging in once the VGA cord is plugged in, both screens instead say "No signal." Several library faculty have attempted to fix the problem with no success.
Rachael Ferguson
Library Circulation Desk Assistant
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello! Some students have indicated a problem projecting their laptop screens onto the televisions in room 207. Instead of displaying a screen to allow logging in once the VGA cord is plugged in, both screens instead say "No signal." Several library faculty have attempted to fix the problem with no success. 

Rachael Ferguson
Library Circulation Desk Assistant

helpdesk-note.body:
I'm guessing 1 of 2 things:
VGA cord is unplugged from monitor Source is set to HDMI or something else on the Monitor.
Check those first, and then continue to troubleshoot if that doesn't solve the issue.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
I'm guessing 1 of 2 things:
  1. VGA cord is unplugged from monitor
  2. Source is set to HDMI or something else on the Monitor.
Check those first, and then continue to troubleshoot if that doesn't solve the issue.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey John,
First of all, your password is going to expire in 2 hours. You should change it when you get this email. If it is too late, you will need to contact the Helpdesk to reset your password.
Now, on to the Outlook issue.
Does Outlook actually receive emails for your regular hornburgj@msoe.edu account? It sounds to me like you may have invalid credentials saved for your Outlook account.
Do you see the other account when you log into Webmail? (outlook.com/msoe)
Global Protect is the VPN that MSOE uses when you need to access things that are on campus from off campus. This is probably not related to any email issues.
helpdesk-note.body-html:

helpdesk-note.body:
I have zero experience with the RPC, the G drive, as well as the Solidview software/license. User's password is still good for a week, he was not locked out. He had access to the internet and the G drive (is that RPC specific?). Is there anything wrong with the Solidview license?

It sounds like he may not be connected to the network. Have tier two go to the RPC to troubleshoot, whoever goes over there can call me if they need to

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Re: [#INC-7820] IT/Networking Ticket
helpdesk-ticket.description:
If one first connects in the south east corner, the issue (of connection but no internet) persists for some distance through the great room, requring a venture as far as the bathrooms on the northeast corner before Internet is obtained. Should one venture in from another location where they were already connected, there is a chance that they will not be disconnected.
It should be noted that this issue is sporadic and random, occurring at random times to random devices that connect, show they are connected, and can not access the Internet.

This is a ticket in place of Mac Wright for being unable to access the internet with a wireless connection in the South East corner of the Great Room. helpdesk-note.body-html:
Ryan,

The account referenced in this incident is a freshservice account.  Freshservice is the ticketing system that the MSOE Help Desk uses to track issues.  This is not an email account. 

Your MSOE email address you used while in school, louzatir@msoe.edu, has been deactivated per school policy, 90 days after you graduated.  You will no longer be able to access, or send and receive emails, from that mailbox.  Since it is past the 90 days, the only step I could take is to create a file of all the emails that were already sent to your loutatir@msoe.edu mailbox.  This does not allow for any new emails to be received by louzatir@msoe.edu to show up in that .PST file.  You will no longer be able to access, or send and receive emails, from louzatir@msoe.edu.  You will need an Outlook client in order to use the .PST file with all of the emails that were in your mailbox on the day the .PST file was created.  When you have an Outlook client, and you successfully attach the .PST file, you will still not be able to access, or send and receive emails, from louzatir@msoe.edu.  You will only be able to view all of the emails that were in louzatir@msoe.edu at the time the .PST file was created.  The .PST file also contains the list of contacts you had in louzatir@msoe.edu.

April 15th, 2016 you successfully created your alumni email account, louzatir@alumni.msoe.edu.  This is a Google account and is not the same as louzatir@msoe.edu.  You will no longer be able to access, or send and receive emails, from louzatir@msoe.edu. Your alumni account, louzatir@alumni.msoe.edu, is your MSOE email address from now on.  Any correspondence that was going on in louzatir@msoe.edu will not be automatically be transferred to your alumni account.  You must take action to make that happen.  Use your current alumni email address, louzatir@alumni.msoe.edu, to contact everyone you wish to continue corresponding with.  Tell them you have a new email address, and to please update their address book to avoid any lost emails.

With this information, I am going to consider this incident as resolved.  Please respond with any further questions you may have.

Peter Pfister
Help Desk Coordinator
414.277.7202

Hi IT,
We just had some students try to print off a 6 page color document and the printer just kept spouting out multiple copies. I believe they canceled the print job after receiving 22 pages. They are concerned about being charged for the pages they didn’t want.
This problem has come up before. Does anyone have any ideas why it spontaneously decides to provide multiple copies?
Perhaps it would be worth the time and expense to go back to having an industrial printer/scanner/copier that can handle color. I don’t remember having so many problems when we did.
Thank you!
Sarah Rowell, MLIS Librarian I MSOE Walter Schroeder Library 414-277-7389 rowell@msoe.edu<mailto:rowell@msoe.edu>

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Good morning – please see below for Dr. Durant’s specific requirements for this meeting.
I will bring a good USB microphone and video camera and run the WebEx meeting from my laptop. Will I be able to plug into the room speakers so that the remote participants can be heard loud enough? Will an LCD projector/screen be available in the Schroeder Room so that I can project meeting materials? Is the WiFi in the Schroeder Room reliable, or should I request a wired connection?
Carole Kasprzycki Administrative Assistant Mathematics Department Electrical Engineering & Computer Science Department Milwaukee School of Engineering 414-277-7452

Will an LCD projector/screen be available in the Schroeder Room so that I can project meeting materials? Is the WiFi in the Schroeder Room reliable, or should I request a wired connection?
 
 
Carole Kasprzycki

Milwaukee School of Engineering
414-277-7452

helpdesk-note.body: Sent to A/V.
helpdesk-note.body-html: Sent to A/V.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Carole Kasprzycki,
The Schroeder Room does have a projector. It is always best to have a wired connection, and there is one available in the room. Also, it is best to use the conference phone setup we have, even though you will be running the WebEx from the computer. You can still run it from the laptop and project from there. If you have the conference phone dial-in as a participant, and then mute the laptop mic, you will get better quality sound and more reliable connection. Also, there are no room speakers in the Schroeder Room. If you use the conference phone, the built-in speakers will be loud enough for everyone to hear. If you wanted to try the USB microphone from the laptop instead, you could mute the conference phone microphone, and just use it for sound - but I'm not sure if there might be a delay over VoIP. A final option would be to connect a good set of external speakers to the laptop for sound (if you didn't want to use the conference phone). We currently do not have any, so you would have to provide your own.
I hope this information is helpful. I would be happy to meet with Dr. Durant or talk by phone if that were easier. Let me know what you would like to do, and I can make sure you have everything you need.
Sincerely,
Andrew M. Holmes, M.Ed Instructional Technology Office: CC307 o: 414-277-6765 c: 414-312-1383 email: holmes@msoe.edu Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/7941

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Virus scan
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Afternoon Helpdesk,
Mark Hoelzer here - from the MSOE Center for BioMolecular Modeling on the 2nd floor of the CC-buildling (room 202). We have a desktop computer running Windows Vista that for a long time has sat unused. I recently cleaned it off and got it back up and running as a student worker workstation.
It seems to work beautifully, connecting to all drives quickly and running programs well. . . except that every little while it suddenly and unpredictably freezes - so completely that the only way to free it is a hard reset. This freezing doesn't seem to be associated with any specific program or action (at least that I can tell). My only guess is that there is some malware or virus on it from years ago that is causing a problem.
So would it be possible to have someone look at it and run a standard virus scan? Or do whatever else might help diagnose the problem. Unfortunately, this freezing is so unpredictable and frequent enough to render the workstation unusable for much.
Thanks as always!
-Mark
PS: I am usually in the office 8-4 every day except Friday.
MSOE Center for BioMolecular Modeling - http://cbm.msoe.edu 3D Molecular Designs - www.3dmoleculardesigns.com<http://www.3dmoleculardesigns.com> hoelzer@msoe.edu office: 414-277-4554 cell: 414-640-8668

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Unable to print in color
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello IT,
I have just spoken with Sheila Barber, whom I was told was checking my account regarding the discrepancy between what your department and student accounts says I have in credit on my Raider account (which is perhaps why my color print jobs are sent but not actually being printed?) Sheila said I have money on my account and that the problem is on IT’s end. I just added even more money today so I should have sufficient funds to draw from.
The ball appears to be back in your court. I am trying to be patient, but this has gone on for a while now and I would really like to be able to print in color myself instead of asking co-workers to do it for me. If they can print in color, why can’t I?
Also, I have not heard any kind of explanation for why the color printer occasionally prints out several more copies of a sent color document than was requested. Could an instance of that be the reason why your records indicated that my account was overdrawn?
Please let me know if there is anything I can do to facilitate the progress of this ticket. Thomas S. has been very helpful in trying to figure this out, but I feel perhaps this needs to be seen by the next tier of IT and Sheila suggested it would fall under Jason’s purview.
Thank you very much for your assistance with this matter,
Sarah Rowell, MLIS Librarian I MSOE Walter Schroeder Library 414-277-7389 rowell@msoe.edu<mailto:rowell@msoe.edu>

Dear Thomas:
The MSOE Financial Aid Office has received your processed FAFSA and is pleased to offer financial aid to assist you in meeting your educational expenses for the 2016-2017 academic year.
To view your award offer, please visit http://myfinancialaid.msoe.edu. You will need your MSOE user name and password to login.
IMPORTANT NOTE: In order to access your financial aid information, please register your @msoe.edu account on the MSOE Community site if you have not already done so. This process creates a link via Single Sign On from your @msoe.edu account to myFinancialAid.
Authentication takes place behind the firewall and no passwords are stored on the MSOE Community.
For your reference, the “Claiming Your Financial Aid Award” brochure under the Forms & Resources section on your “My Financial Aid” site can assist with many frequently asked questions. Please read and carefully follow the instructions in the brochure.
Your award is based on the following enrollment levels:
Full-time for the Fall term
Full-time for the Winter term
Full-time for the Spring term.
If your enrollment level changes, we asked that you notify the Financial Aid Office so that we may adjustment your award offer to reflect your enrollment status, if necessary.
If you wish to adjust any previously accepted/declined aid listed online, please use our online form at: www.msoe.edu/accept-your-award
Lastly, we ask that you also notify us if you are receiving or expect to receive aid that is not contained in this award offer.
If you have any questions or concerns, please contact our office.
Sincerely,
MSOE Financial Aid Office
414-277-7223
finaid@msoe.edu

Thomas Hill
606 GREENWAY TER
HARTLAND, Wisconsin 53029

helpdesk-ticket.description: User reports that his Ansys software is not getting a license. The error says that the License manager software is out of date. He has tried uninstalling and reinstalling with no luck.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: User reports that his Ansys software is not getting a license. The error says that the License manager software is out of date. He has tried uninstalling and reinstalling with no luck.

helpdesk-note.body: Mike Timm shows the license expires on Aug 17.
helpdesk-note.body-html: Mike Timm shows the license expires on Aug 17.

helpdesk-note.body:
I was able to recreate the user's error. The exact error message reads:
"Your version of the ANSYS license manager software is out of date. Please download and install the current ANSYS license manager from the ANSYS Customer Portal.
The version of the license server 2325@AppLicense.msoe.edu [1.2.0] must be greater or equal to the client ANS_WB version [1.4.0]."
I believe that it wouldn't hurt to check applicense to see if upgrading the ansys lic manager will fix our issue. Let me know what you think, I am trying to think back to last summer and how we went around this error, I thought last summer this error could be ignored and the user was actually able to pull a license. I will look through my old test excel sheets and see if I find any notes.
-Sam

helpdesk-note.body: It should be pointing to applicense2.msoe.edu not applicense.msoe.edu
helpdesk-note.body-html: It should be pointing to applicense2.msoe.edu not applicense.msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Daniel,
Here is a possible solution for your issue. It is basically just uninstalling and reinstalling Ansys but with an important change of steps in the installation process.
1) Completely Uninstall All Ansys software. 2) Start the re-installation process by following the guide attached to this email. 3) When you reach step 15 in the guide and it asks you to input the license server information under Hostname 1 type in: applicense2.msoe.edu 4) All the other steps in the guide should be the same aside from step 15.
Please let me know if you run into any other problems with the installation process or with pulling a license key. Also I know the image quality in the guide is pretty poor so don't be afraid to ask if you need me to clarify something for you.
Best Regards, Sam West MSOE IT

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Dr. Joshua Schultz,
I'm sorry about the delay. We're not entirely sure the source of the error, it looks like it is a file permission issue. Ideally, if you are set as the administrator on the laptop you should be able to write to any folder. If you go to Start>Control Panel>User Accounts>User Accounts>Manage User Accounts you should see your username in the list and it being in the Administrators group. If you aren't, it will prompt you before you are even able to get into Manage User Accounts and will refuse your password.
Otherwise if you are an admin, you may have to try a full uninstall and reinstall of Ansys. Abby Griffin

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Please see the email I sent to AV this morning.
Dr. Russ Meier, Ph.D., Professor Electrical Engineering and Computer Science Milwaukee School of Engineering 1025 N. Broadway Milwaukee, WI 53202 USA +1 414 277 2243 meier@msoe.edu
IGIP International Engineering Educator Honoris Causa (ING.PAED.IGIP h.c.) MSOE Distinguished Teaching Professor
From: Russ Meier <meier@msoe.edu> Date: Wednesday, May 11, 2016 at 10:30 AM To: AV <AV@msoe.edu>, "Lewis, Willie" <lewisw@msoe.edu>, "Bailey, Susan" <baileysk@msoe.edu>, "Cliff, Jessica Z." <cliff@msoe.edu> Cc: "Pfister, Peter" <pfister@msoe.edu> Subject: IEEE Event: Thursday, May 12, 2016
Hello team:
This email confirms that 100 students and engineers from Milwaukee will converge on the Todd Wehr Auditorium tomorrow night for the IEEE Milwaukee Section Poster Competition and Keynote Address. All parties should verify their responsibilities and ensure we are ready to go. I have heard from everyone EXCEPT AV – thus, IT – please pay close attention to this email and work with me to finalize your part of the event.
· Officer Lewis extended blanket parking to the Broadway lots. Officer Lewis – can we have the Todd Wehr doors and the President’s Conference Room unlocked by 4:30 p.m. and remain unlocked until 8:30 p.m?
· Sue Bailey and I met yesterday and discussed the chair / table layouts. Jessica Cliff communicated with Sue regarding catering needs. Sue Bailey and her team will set classroom style chairs for 72 in rows of 6: leaving space along the auditorium edge for poster easels and question/answer discussions.
· Jessica Cliff and her team are responsible for catering / bar area. Legal age participants will be able to purchase beer with cash bar only. Jessica will ensure that cash bar is ready to go and that the catering of appetizers begins at 6:00 p.m.
· AV needs: laptop computer, podium, handheld mic, lav mic at front of auditorium. Projectors on with laptop displaying MSOE background logo with sleep settings off by 5:30 p.m. If IT has easels, I prefer to use them rather than EECS easels. I would need 25 easels minimum. Please let me know if you have easels that can hold foam core / frames.
Please acknowledge receipt of this email with reply-only to me to help avoid cluttering team member’s mailboxes.
Russ

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Question regarding AV in the Todd Wehr
helpdesk-ticket.description: How many microphones do we provide in the Todd Wehr? What type of microphones? Do we have wireless Microphones available for checkout, or the ones that you attach to your clothing? Who controls the spot light?
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
How many microphones do we provide in the Todd Wehr?
What type of microphones?
Do we have wireless Microphones available for checkout, or the ones that you attach to your clothing?
Who controls the spot light?

helpdesk-note.body: sending to AV
helpdesk-note.body-html: sending to AV

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi alawfir,
We have 2 wireless handheld microphones that we generally provide by default. In addition, there is a lavaliere (attachable) microphone that is available. We have additional wired microphones if needed. These include instrument microphones and pencil condenser microphones that are useful for instrument amplification. These microphones are not available for checkout beyond the Todd Wehr. We do, however, have a portable PA system that includes a wireless handheld microphone that can be used for other events.
AV is currently not involved with the lighting in the Todd Wehr. I would suggest contacting Professor Ed Griggs and/or student theatre troupe, student advisor, Savanna Neue, who generally take care of the lighting.
I hope this is helpful. Please let me know if we can assist you for any upcoming events at MSOE.
Sincerely,
Andrew M. Holmes, M.Ed Instructional Technology Office: CC307 email: holmes@msoe.edu phone: x6765 Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8047
How many microphones do we provide in the Todd Wehr? What type of microphones? Do we have wireless Microphones available for checkout, or the ones that you attach to your clothing? Who controls the spot light?
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi alawfir,

We have 2 wireless handheld microphones that we generally provide by default.  In addition, there is a lavaliere (attachable) microphone that is available.  We have additional wired microphones if needed.  These include instrument microphones and pencil condenser microphones that are useful for instrument amplification.  These microphones are not available for checkout beyond the Todd Wehr.  We do, however, have a portable PA system that includes a wireless handheld microphone that can be used for other events.

AV is currently not involved with the lighting in the Todd Wehr.  I would suggest contacting Professor Ed Griggs and/or student theatre troupe, student advisor, Savanna Neue, who generally take care of the lighting.

I hope this is helpful.  Please let me know if we can assist you for any upcoming events at MSOE.

Sincerely,

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Outlook Clutter
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Is there a way IT can block MSOE to MSOE emails from entering the clutter folder? The Financial Aid Office sends important announcements to students and we have noticed in conversations with students that these messages are ending up their clutter folder.
Thanks for considering,
Steve Midthun Assoc.Director of Financial Aid MSOE- Financial Aid Office (CC431) 1025 N Broadway Milwaukee, WI 53202 midthun@msoe.edu<mailto:midthun@msoe.edu> 414-277-7224
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Is there a way IT can block MSOE to MSOE emails from entering the clutter folder?  The Financial Aid Office sends important announcements to students and we have noticed in conversations with students that these messages are ending up their clutter folder.
 
Thanks for considering,
 
Steve Midthun
Assoc.Director of Financial Aid
MSOE- Financial Aid Office (CC431)
1025 N Broadway
Milwaukee, WI 53202
midthun@msoe.edu
414-277-7224

helpdesk-note.body:
Outlook will move emails to clutter that are consistently ignored for a period of time and if no response is given to the sender. So the students whom this is an issue for did this to themselves by not reading the emails that financial aid sends to them. Also it takes like two seconds to change clutter settings.
To change settings all a user has to do is: 1) Log into Outlook Web App 2) Click on the top right corner Settings>Options>Mail>Automatic Processing>Clutter
Also if Finaid marked their emails as important with the red little flag, outlook would be less likely to move those emails to clutter.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Outlook will move emails to clutter that are consistently ignored for a period of time and if no response is given to the sender. So the students whom this is an issue for did this to themselves by not reading the emails that financial aid sends to them. Also it takes like two seconds to change clutter settings. 

To change settings all a user has to do is:
1) Log into Outlook Web App
2) Click on the top right corner Settings>Options>Mail>Automatic Processing>Clutter

Also if Finaid marked their emails as important with the red little flag, outlook would be less likely to move those emails to clutter.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Steve Midthun, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/8050
The way the clutter box works is that when an email from a particular sender is ignored for a period of time, Outlook flags that and next time it comes in it gets sent to clutter. There is nothing we are able to do to stop this from happening. If a student would like to stop the clutter box from doing that, they only need to follow these steps:
1) Log into Outlook Web App 2) Click on the top right corner Settings>Options>Mail>Automatic Processing>Clutter
Also, if your office would like to prevent things from going to clutter all together, you could mark any email that the student Needs to see as important. This will lessen the chance that the outlook app will find these and move them to clutter.
If you have any questions let us know.
James Windorff Helpdesk Technician helpdesk@msoe.edu 414 277 7288

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Jasmine – I’m trying to update the statements (with our current logo – and other information) but I’m having a hard time figuring out how this statement is being generated – more specifically with IM “report” it’s pulling so I can update accordingly. Can you help me with this, please?
Thanks, Stacey

helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Jasmine – I’m trying to update the statements (with our current logo – and other information) but I’m having a hard time figuring out how this statement is being generated – more specifically with IM “report” it’s pulling so I can update accordingly.  Can you help me with this, please? 
 
Thanks,
Stacey

helpdesk-note.body: updating to database team
helpdesk-note.body-html: updating to database team

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Stacey,
The InfoMaker report for the MSOE Course and Fee Statement is sort of living here in the cloud: D:\MSOE\Jenzabar\Reports\Custom\ARReport.pbl - r_statements_layouts1_debe_mse. By 'sort of', I mean that this is where you can make changes to the report but there is another step to actually put the report on myMSOE. The next step is for Mike to copy the report to a 'special/secret' pbl that houses all the myMSOE reports.
I added the updated logo for you already, but you can still edit this report more if you need to. Once you are done making changes to the r_statements_layouts1_debe_mse report, you can create a ticket (or respond to this one :) ) and ask me to put the updated report on myMSOE.
Here is a screen shot of what I see in the report now on myMSOE:
FYI- I did find the original report. It is still in your ARReport.pbl. It's called r_statements_layout1. It is pulling the same dates as our customized report but check it out and let me know if you still want to go back to using that. I really think the customized report will be fine though. It's just a matter of using the Subsidiary Controls correctly. I was also able to sign up for a free tutorial with Jenzabar Student Billing. I'm not sure if that will solve our Subsidiary Control questions but it's a good start. What I did notice that was different with the original report is that period_end_date was listed as Date: see below. So maybe the period_end_dte in Subsidiary Code should be the date you run reports rather than 05/31? (from the original report)
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Stacey, 

The InfoMaker report for the MSOE Course and Fee Statement is sort of living here in the cloud:  D:\MSOE\Jenzabar\Reports\Custom\ARReport.pbl - r_statements_layouts1_debe_mse. By 'sort of', I mean that this is where you can make changes to the report but there is another step to actually put the report on myMSOE. The next step is for Mike to copy the report to a 'special/secret' pbl that houses all the myMSOE reports.

I added the updated logo for you already, but you can still edit this report more if you need to. Once you are done making changes to the r_statements_layouts1_debe_mse report, you can create a ticket (or respond to this one :) ) and ask me to put the updated report on myMSOE. 

Here is a screen shot of what I see in the report now on myMSOE: 



FYI- I did find the original report. It is still in your ARReport.pbl. It's called r_statements_layout1. It is pulling the same dates as our customized report but check it out and let me know if you still want to go back to using that. I really think the customized report will be fine though. It's just a matter of using the Subsidiary Controls correctly. I was also able to sign up for a free tutorial with Jenzabar Student Billing. I'm not sure if that will solve our Subsidiary Control questions but it's a good start. What I did notice that was different with the original report is that period_end_date was listed as Date: see below. So maybe the period_end_dte in Subsidiary Code should be the date you run reports rather than 05/31?
 (from the original report)
